#X text 286 484 This is the exact same basic monophonic subtractive synth from a few examples before. Open [pd subtractive] for the details., f 28;
#X text 250 446 actual modulation frequency;
#X text 48 21 And now it's time to use Ring Modulation in Synthesis as an effects processor \, which is quite common. For this patch \, we have also do keyboard tracking to control the modulation frequency. So instead of having a fixed harmonic relationship like before we have less control of the harmonic outcome specially because that's the interesting thing about Ring Modulation. If you decrease the tracking amount you get a fixed modulation frequency., f 66;
